column4: How do I terminate a program that doesn't respond, I cannot find the process name of that program....
How do I kill a process which is frozen but I don't know the name of it?...
can someone please help me!...
I have a program that has frozen, I cannot close it
I asked twice already
don't know the name of it
I don't know what the process name is
what program is frozen?
it doesn't show me anything frozen
package manager
the one that installs deb files
not symantec
the deb file installer
it says package installer
I remember there was a way to target process
you type a command
then drag a skull to a program and kill it
That worked but, I always have this problem with killing processes
I don't always know their name, and they are often named different like package manager is gdebi how am I supposed ot know that?
is there a way to target the frozen application?
yes
did anyone mention it?
No one told me about xkill
Clicking the close button on a rozen program will often bring up a dialog asking if you wnat to force a quit.
